div1.p: In the district court of the Third Judicial District of Washington Territory holding terms at Seattle for the counties of King and Kitsak
div1.ab: In the matter of the application of Henry Imhoff for a writ of Habeas Corpus
div1.p: The United States of America sends Greeting to L.V. Wyckoff

We command you that you have the body of Henry Imhoff by you restrained of his liberty and make known the cause of such restraint before the Honorable John P. Hoyt Judge of the Second Judicial District in the Territory of Washington at his chambers in the city of Seattle on Monday the tenth day of November at 7 o'clock P.M. to do and recieve what shall then + there considered concerning the said Henry Imhoff And have you then and there this writ.
div1.ab: Witness the Honorable John P. Hoyt, Judge of the Second Judicial District in the Territory of Washington and the seal of said court this 7th day of November A.D. 1881
No. 276 In District Court King Co In the Matter of the Application of Henry Imhoff for a Writ of Habeas Corpus Writ-
Filed November 10, 1881 James Seavey, Clerk. By James P. Ludlow Deputy Clerk.
